&lt;h2&gt;


&lt;strong&gt;3. Server Components: Enhancing Performance&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Server Components allow developers to offload part of the rendering workload to the server. By doing so, they reduce the amount of JavaScript sent to the client, improving performance and time-to-interactivity.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;


&lt;strong&gt;Key Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Smaller JavaScript bundles.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Faster page loads, especially on slower networks.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Improved SEO with server-side rendering.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: Using Server Components&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class="highlight js-code-highlight"&gt;
&lt;pre class="highlight javascript"&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;// Profile.server.js&lt;/span&gt;
