&lt;span class="p"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;



&lt;p&gt;With the new optimisations, React minimizes the number of components that need to re-render when context values change.&lt;/p&gt;




&lt;h2&gt;


&lt;strong&gt;6. Support for Custom Elements&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Custom elements (web components) are now fully supported in React 19. This opens up new possibilities for reusing components across different frameworks or libraries.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: Using a Custom Element in React&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;
