&lt;p&gt;React 19 bridges the gap between React components and native web components, enabling seamless interoperability.&lt;/p&gt;




&lt;h2&gt;


&lt;strong&gt;7. Migration and Best Practices&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Migrating to React 19 is straightforward for most projects. Here are some tips to ensure a smooth transition:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Upgrade Dependencies&lt;/strong&gt;: Update all third-party libraries to their latest versions.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use Feature Flags&lt;/strong&gt;: Gradually adopt new features using feature flags to avoid unexpected issues.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Test Thoroughly&lt;/strong&gt;: Test your application in staging environments to identify and fix compatibility issues.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To upgrade:&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class="highlight js-code-highlight"&gt;
